caption: Inconsistent hours make it the biggest pain when the next nearest open starbucks is a 10 minute drive to Forest Park. They're open some weekends, closed the next. Make up your mind! It's AMAZING how inherent discrimination has become during this pandemic. I was just asked to put on a mask in addition to my face shield, but I look over and a Caucasian woman is sitting inside enjoying her entire meal, even though it says the stations are closed for seating or dining inside.  I guess rules only apply to certain groups/demographics of people...so disheartening!!!  The sad part is I live above this establishment and frequent it often...guess I won't anymore!

I was visiting from out of town and looking for a place to cool down. I normally get a cold brew, but after talking to Taylor, she told me how it tasted and tried to match my taste to a thirst quenching drink I might like.  Taylor also made sure right when I arrived that she was ready to help me and my family and if I needed any help before ordering. She seems like a sweet, kind, and down to earth individual that made my short visit one I could feel comfortable in and enjoy my stay.  Give that woman a raise!!! By far my favorite barista I've ever met!!! She made this place her own by how she welcomeded each person, moved to the beat of the music in the cafe to set the mood in creating sweet drinks with a kick of music love, and did I mention my drink was DELICIOUS!!!! I've never tried the Mango Drangonfruit refresher, but sure glad I took Taylor's advice. Each Starbucks has a slightly different feel and decor, but Taylor brightens this place up and will go far in life in how she carries herself wherever she may go.  Thank you Taylor and Starbuvks for being a part of my day and our St. Louis trip. Putting this Starbucks on the map!!!

Seating is fairly plentiful but a bit close quarters.  There are several outdoor tables but no drive-thru.  Customer service here is much improved lately, with staff addressing regular customers by name and warmly greeting newcomers.

If you're going to go to Starbucks in downtown St. Louis, go to this one. It's the only one owned by the company and 1000 times better than the one in the Renaissance Hotel.  It's the usual Starbucks fare, with an efficient and very nice staff. If anything, the shop is smaller than the average Starbucks so finding a seat can be a challenge when it's not possible to utilize the tables outside. Other than that, it's worth the trip to go to this location and stay away from the one on Washington street.

This is my favorite Starbucks in downtown STL.  The people are always great and friendly.  They come across as "happy to see you."   The place great for the road office only if your lucky enough to snatch a good seat close to an electrical outlet. I wish it was larger and would accommodate more people.  Parking can be a challenge but I have always nabbed a spot on the west side, just watch your meter!  Great place to get work done and enjoy people watching out the window.  If you ever show up and need to get some work done but the place is busy just look out the door and check the place out across the street, get your cup of joe and go over there. :}
